{{Lunisolar November}} '''Lunisolar November''' (旧暦十一月) is the eleventh {{ill|Month (Calendar)|ja|月 (暦)|lt=Month|lt_ja=月|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} of the year in the {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Lunisolar calendar|ja|太陰太陽暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}).
The month that includes the {{ill|Winter Solstice|ja|冬至|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} becomes November. In the {{ill|New Calendar|ja|新暦|1=New Calendar (Japan)|lt=New Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, it corresponds approximately to late {{ill|November|ja|11月|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} to early {{ill|January|ja|1月|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
Another name for November is {{nihongo|'''Shimozuki'''|しもつき}}. The origin of the name is explained in {{ill|November|ja|11月|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. An alternative name is “Chūtō (仲冬)”.
In the Eastern lunisolar calendar, because the number of days in a month, known as {{ill|Large and Small|ja|大小|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (with large months having 30 days and small months 29 days), varies by year, there are years when November ends on the 29th and no November 30th exists.
